      "span_text": "In the color task, before numerosity training, color discrimination performance ( Figure 1C ) was well above chance for both monkeys (monkey L: 99.19% ± 0.24%; monkey S: 97.93% ± 0.34%; binomial test; p < 0.001) for all color combinations (as reported previously in [CITATION_1] )."
